<section class="section">
  <div class="section-heading">
    <p class="eyebrow">Why ShipFlow Exists</p>
    <h2>The main problem is not slower coding. It is weaker execution.</h2>
    <p>
      Solo founders already know how to ship. The real drag appears when the
      context leaks, the handoff gets fuzzy, and every new agent thread starts
      paying the same ambiguity bill again.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card-grid">
    {
      features.map((feature) => (
        <article class="card">
          <h3>{feature.title}</h3>
          <p>{feature.body}</p>
        </article>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>
